  {
    "number": 10064,
    "title": "[trace] optimize loading",
    "body": "Land a few optimizations to the trace server\n\n* Change `SpanEvent` so it is 16 bytes instead of 24 bytes by triggering a `niche` optimization\n* Change `args` and `events` to be a `smallvec` with inline size 1\n  * for `args` it is size &lt;=1 ~31% of the time\n  * for `events` it is size &lt;=1 69% of the time\n* Compute min/max timestamps in a single pass instead of 2 when inserting into the selftimetree\n* Bundle dynamically computed &#39;total&#39; fields behind a single OnceLock\n   * saves 40 bytes per span due to Oncelock overheads\n\n\nMeasuring with one 14gb trace file I see loading times progress from 96.8s (42g of ram) s to 81.9s (27G of ram).\n\n",
    "state": "open",
    "draft": false,
    "merged": false,
    "html_url": "https://github.com/example-org/sample-app/pull/10064",
